{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-opus-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_013TanLRa18iTRR5PmTPa9Tc", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Now I have all the information needed. Let me write the codebase map."}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 12666, "cache_read_input_tokens": 24663, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 12666, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "bed6cddb-eae5-42c5-9d20-343203fe2346", "uuid": "76771868-f0a1-48f2-98f0-9b97907d5814", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcLNhjjr5NGijn1edoV6b", "timestamp": "2026-06-23T14:47:59.287Z"}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-opus-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_013TanLRa18iTRR5PmTPa9Tc", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_01NdqqGCXhCxuY5HNDQcLhkF", "name": "Write", "input": {"file_path": "/private/var/folders/38/_z2xr8rn0m33jpdp5jkbmd500000gn/T/agent-eval/2026-06-23-opus/cases/case-003-edge-minimal-repo/output/agent-output.md", "content": "# Codebase Map\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\n.\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 main.py              # Flask application \u2014 the only source file\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 input.yaml           # Evaluation harness metadata (not app code)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 requirements.txt     # Python dependencies (Flask, Gunicorn)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 hooks/\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 subagent_stop.py # Claude Code hook \u2014 copies agent transcripts\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 output/              # Empty directory for skill/agent output\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 CLAUDE.md            # Symlink \u2192 external agent-lab CLAUDE.md\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 scripts/             # Symlink \u2192 external agent-lab scripts\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 skills/              # Symlink \u2192 external agent-lab skills\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 .claude/             # Claude Code project settings\n```\n\nThis is a **minimal single-file Python repository**. The symlinks (`CLAUDE.md`, `scripts/`, `skills/`) point to an external Obsidian vault (`~/Obsidian/tsd-agent-lab/`) and are part of the evaluation harness, not the application.\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n**Pattern:** Single-file Flask microservice with in-memory state.\n\n- **Entry point:** `main.py` \u2014 a Flask app serving a REST API on port 8080.\n- **Endpoints:**\n  - `GET /health` \u2014 returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n  - `GET /users` \u2014 returns all users as a JSON list\n  - `POST /users` \u2014 creates a user (requires `{\"name\": \"...\"}` in body), returns 201\n- **Data store:** In-memory Python dict (`users`); global counter (`next_id`) for auto-increment IDs. All data is lost on restart.\n- **No database, no ORM, no auth, no middleware, no config files, no tests.**\n\n## Build and Test Commands\n\n| Action | Command |\n|--------|---------|\n| Install deps | `pip install -r requirements.txt` |\n| Run (dev) | `python main.py` |\n| Run (prod) | `gunicorn main:app -b 0.0.0.0:8080` |\n| Test | *None \u2014 no test files or test framework configured* |\n| Lint | *None \u2014 no linter configured* |\n\n## Key Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| Flask | 3.0.0 | Web framework \u2014 provides routing, request parsing, JSON responses |\n| Gunicorn | 21.2.0 | Production WSGI server (listed but no Procfile/entrypoint configured) |\n\nNo transitive dependencies of note. No lock file (`requirements.lock`, `Pipfile.lock`, etc.) is present.\n\n## Risk Areas\n\n1. **No persistence.** The in-memory `users` dict and `next_id` counter reset on every restart. Any production use requires a database.\n2. **No tests.** Zero test coverage \u2014 no test framework is even listed in dependencies.\n3. **Global mutable state.** `next_id` uses `global` and is not thread-safe. Under Gunicorn with multiple workers, each worker gets its own `users` dict and `next_id` counter, causing ID collisions and data inconsistency.\n4. **No input validation beyond `name` presence.** No length limits, type checking, or sanitization on user input.\n5. **No authentication or authorization.** All endpoints are publicly accessible.\n6. **No README or documentation.** The `input.yaml` describes this as \"a barely documented repository.\"\n7. **No `.gitignore`.** Missing ignores for `__pycache__`, `.venv`, etc.\n\n## Recommended First Tasks\n\n1. **Add a test suite.** Install `pytest` and write tests for the three endpoints (`/health`, `GET /users`, `POST /users` including the 400 error case). This is the highest-value first step \u2014 it enables safe iteration.\n2. **Add a `.gitignore`.** Create a standard Python `.gitignore` to exclude `__pycache__/`, `*.pyc`, `.venv/`, etc.\n3. **Fix thread-safety of `next_id`.** Replace the global counter with `threading.Lock` or use UUIDs, so the app behaves correctly under multi-worker Gunicorn.\n4. **Add a `README.md`.** Document what the project is, how to run it, and the available API endpoints.\n5. **Add input validation.** Validate `name` length/type and reject unexpected fields in `POST /users`.\n"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 12666, "cache_read_input_tokens": 24663, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 12666, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "bed6cddb-eae5-42c5-9d20-343203fe2346", "uuid": "e64f4979-1424-4aa4-8b64-38a64157a73b", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcLNhjjr5NGijn1edoV6b", "timestamp": "2026-06-23T14:48:20.571Z"}
