"}` in body), returns 201\n- **Data store:** In-memory Python dict (`users`); global counter (`next_id`) for auto-increment IDs. All data is lost on restart.\n- **No database, no ORM, no auth, no middleware, no config files, no tests.**\n\n## Build and Test Commands\n\n| Action | Command |\n|--------|---------|\n| Install deps | `pip install -r requirements.txt` |\n| Run (dev) | `python main.py` |\n| Run (prod) | `gunicorn main:app -b 0.0.0.0:8080` |\n| Test | *None — no test files or test framework configured* |\n| Lint | *None — no linter configured* |\n\n## Key Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| Flask | 3.0.0 | Web framework — provides routing, request parsing, JSON responses |\n| Gunicorn | 21.2.0 | Production WSGI server (listed but no Procfile/entrypoint configured) |\n\nNo transitive dependencies of note. No lock file (`requirements.lock`, `Pipfile.lock`, etc.) is present.\n\n## Risk Areas\n\n1. **No persistence.** The in-memory `users` dict and `next_id` counter reset on every restart. Any production use requires a database.\n2. **No tests.** Zero test coverage — no test framework is even listed in dependencies.\n3. **Global mutable state.** `next_id` uses `global` and is not thread-safe. Under Gunicorn with multiple workers, each worker gets its own `users` dict and `next_id` counter, causing ID collisions and data inconsistency.\n4. **No input validation beyond `name` presence.** No length limits, type checking, or sanitization on user input.\n5. **No authentication or authorization.** All endpoints are publicly accessible.\n6. **No README or documentation.** The `input.yaml` describes this as \"a barely documented repository.\"\n7. **No `.gitignore`.** Missing ignores for `__pycache__`, `.venv`, etc.\n\n## Recommended First Tasks\n\n1. **Add a test suite.** Install `pytest` and write tests for the three endpoints (`/health`, `GET /users`, `POST /users` including the 400 error case). This is the highest-value first step — it enables safe iteration.\n2. **Add a `.gitignore`.** Create a standard Python `.gitignore` to exclude `__pycache__/`, `*.pyc`, `.venv/`, etc.\n3. **Fix thread-safety of `next_id`.** Replace the global counter with `threading.Lock` or use UUIDs, so the app behaves correctly under multi-worker Gunicorn.\n4. **Add a `README.md`.** Document what the project is, how to run it, and the available API endpoints.\n5. **Add input validation.** Validate `name` length/type and reject unexpected fields in `POST /users`.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
